.mt-2.header-title.text-center.text-dark &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;3. The employee will submit accurate records of employment applications and time cards/route sheets;                                  dl.row.mb-0                                      dd                                          h4.mt-2.header-title.text-center.text-dark &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;4. The employee will conduct themselves in a professional manner in all interactions with supervisors, peers and clients. Licensed and certified employees will hold to the standards of their accrediting board;                                  dl.row.mb-0                                      dd                                          h4.mt-2.header-title.text-center.text-dark &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;5. The employee will respect the right of the property of the agency, other employees and patients.                                  dl.row.mb-0                                      dd                                          h4.mt-2.header-title.text-center.text-dark &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp6. The employee will respect the right of the property of the agency, other employees and patients.                                  dl.row.mb-0                                      dd                                          h4.mt-2.header-title.text-center.text-dark &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp7. The employee will refrain from excessive or unexcused absences;                                  dl.row.mb-0                                      dd                                          h4.mt-2.header-title.text-center.text-dark &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp8. The employee will not engage in any of the following:                                  dl.row.mb-0                                      dd                                          h4.mt-2.header-title.text-center.text-dark &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; a. Negligence,                                  dl.row.mb-0                                      dd                                          h4.mt-2.header-title.text-center.text-dark &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; b. Possession or being under the influence of alcohol or illegal substances, and ,                                  dl.row.mb-0                                      dd                                          h4.mt-2.header-title.text-center.text-dark &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; c. Possession of weapons while on duty                                  dl.row.mb-0                                      dd                                          h4.mt-2.header-title.text-center.text-dark &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp9. The employee will be aware of and practice safety policies and procedures;                                  dl.row.mb-0                                      dd                                          h4.mt-2.header-title.text-center.text-dark &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp10. The employee will perform his/her duties as stipulated in the criteria  based job descriptions.                                  dl.row.mb-0                                      dd                                          h4.mt-2.header-title.text-center.text-dark &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp11. The employee will be aware and adhere to the fraud and abuse laws as stated in the Medicare Act.;                                  dl.row.mb-0                                      dd                                          h4.mt-2.header-title.text-center.text-dark &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp12. The employee will refrain from use of prejudicial or offensive language;                                  dl.row.mb-0                                      dd                                          h4.mt-2.header-title.text-center.text-dark &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp13. No Acceptance of gift of tips;                                  dl.row.mb-0                                      dd                                          h4.mt-2.header-title.text-center.text-dark &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp14. No Friends or relatives brought to the client's home;                                  dl.row.mb-0                                      dd                                          h4.mt-2.header-title.text-center.text-dark &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;15. No Consumption of alcoholic beverages or use of medicine or drugs for any purpose other than medical in the clients home or prior to service of delivery.                                  dl.row.mb-0                                      dd                                          h4.mt-2.header-title.text-center.text-dark &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;16. No Smoking in the client's home (other than in designated areas);                                  dl.row.mb-0                                      dd                                          h4.mt-2.header-title.text-center.text-dark &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;17. No solicitation on acceptance of money or goods from the client;                                  dl.row.mb-0                                      dd                                          h4.mt-2.header-title.text-center.text-dark &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;18. You are expected to call at least (4) hours prior to duty if you are unable to go an assignment for any reason. in addition, you are also requested to call anytime you are doing to be late to an assignment; and                                  dl.row.mb-0                                      dd                                          h4.mt-2.header-title.text-center.text-dark &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;19. Under no circumstances are you to change any part of the services provided to the client. The client or a family member must call in to the office.                                  br                                  br      p.card-text.text-center.text-dark This type of disciplinary action which may be token in response to violation of this code of conduct will be determined on an individual basis to include, but not limited to the following report incidents to licensing agencies where applicable, oral warning, written warning, suspension , without pay, demotion, probation or termination. Violation of the medicare Fraud and Abuse Laws may result in fines of up to $25,000.00 and five (5) years imprisonment.      br      br      h4.mb-3.header-title.text-dark.text-left I have read and agreed to comply with the above Code of Conduct.          br          br          br          br          br          br          br          br          .form-row.col-lg-12              .form-group.col-md-6                  label.text-dark Employee Printed Name :                  input.form-control.waves-float(type='text' value='' name='pg11employeecontractor')              .form-group.col-md-6                  label.text-dark Title                  input.form-control.waves-float(type='text' value='' name='pg11title')          .form-row.col-lg-12              .form-group.col-md-6.text-center                  .card                      .card-body.bg-white                          div.flex.text-center       